	(ipsilesional) and 11.0 +/- 3.3 (contralesional) for yaw impulses
	(mean +/- 95\% confidence intervals). 5. VOR gain (gamma), after
	uVD, were significantly lower than normal for both directions of
	roll, pitch, and yaw impulses and much lower during ipsilesional
	than during contralesional roll and yaw impulses. At 80 ms from the
	onset of the head impulse, the gamma was 0.22 +/- 0.08 (ipsilesional)
