	(delta)], it is significantly different from its corresponding G
	during ipsilesional roll and yaw, and during all pitch impulses,
	but not during contralesional roll and yaw impulses. 6. After uPCO,
	pitch-vertical gamma during pitch-up impulses was reduced to the
	same extent as after uVD; roll-torsional gamma during ipsilesional
	roll impulses was significantly lower than normal but significantly
	higher than after uVD. At 80 ms from the onset of the head impulse,
	gamma was 0.32 +/- 0.13 (ipsilesional) and 0.55 +/- 0.16 (contralesional)
	for roll impulses, 0.51 +/- 0.12 (up) and 0.91 +/- 0.14 (down) for
	pitch impulses, and 0.76 +/- 0.06 (ipsilesional) and 0.73 +/- 0.09
	(contralesional) for yaw impulses (mean +/- 95\% confidence intervals).
	7. The eye rotation axis, after uVD, deviates in the yaw plane, away
	from the normal interaural axis, toward the nasooccipital axis, during
	all pitch impulses. After uPCO, the eye rotation axis deviates in
	same direction as after uVD during pitch-up impulses, but is well
	aligned with the head rotation axis during pitch-down impulses.},
