	7.6 +/- 2.8 (SD) ms for pitch impulses, and 7.5 +/- 2.9 (SD) ms for
	yaw impulses. 7. We conclude that the normal VOR produces eye rotations
	that are almost perfectly compensatory in direction as well as in
	speed, but only during yaw and pitch impulses. During roll impulses,
